mbly in ","service tool T3880171"," in the inverted orientation.","Apply a smear of fork oil to the bushes and new seals.","Position the seals, bushes and a new circlip to the fork inner tube as noted during removal. Make sure that the oil seal (item 3) is positioned with the text end facing the circlip (item 2).","Dust seal","Circlip","Oil seal","Washer","Lower bush","Upper bush","Using a suitable tool, fit the upper bush to the fork inner tube.","Position the inner tube assembly to the outer. Make sure that the oil and dust seal lips do not become damaged.","Use ","service tool T3880447"," to drive the lower bush, washer and oil seal into position. Make sure that the circlip groove is fully visible.","T3880447 - Fork seal Tool 49mm","Install a new circlip to retain the oil seal.","Dust seal","Circlip","Position the dust seal to the outer tube.","Use the wider end of ","service tool T3880157"," with hand pressure only, to press the dust seal into position in the outer tube.","It is much easier to torque the top cap when the fork has been refitted.","Right Hand Fork","Make sure the shims and spring are fitted to the compression rod inner as noted for removal.","Fit the compression rod inner, spring and shims assembly to the fork inner tube.","Compression rod inner assembly","Spring","Shims","Fork inner tube","Fork outer tube","Position the fork outer tube down so the dust seal is in contact with the axle holder and adjust the fork oil level to ","157 mm"," below the upper edge of the outer tube (see ","Fork Oil Change - Oil Refilling",").","Fit the outer assembly to the fork inner tube.","Compression rod outer assembly","Inner bolt","Using ","service tool T3880448"," tighten the fork inner bolt to ","90 Nm",".","T3880448 - Front Fork Inner Bolt Tool","Inner bolt","Fork outer tube","Lubricate the O-ring on the top cap with a smear of fork oil.","Screw the top cap into the outer tube and using service tool tighten to ","35 Nm",".","Left Hand Fork","Fit the fork spring.","Position the fork outer tube down so the dust seal is in contact with the axle holder and adjust the fork oil level to ","97 mm"," below the upper edge of the outer tube (see ","Fork Oil Change - Oil Refilling",").","Adjust the damping rod lock nut to the bottom of the threads.","Fit ","service tool T3880085"," to the damping rod and lift up the damping rod.","T3880085 - Fork Piston Holder","Damping rod","Lock nut","Inner tube","Outer tube","Fit the spring collar.","Fit the spring stopper on top of the spring collar as shown in the illustration below.","Spring collar","Spring stopper","T3880085 - Fork Piston Holder","Fit ","service tool T3880067"," over the spring stopper. Screw in the arms of ","service tool T3880067"," until they positively engage in the spring collar holes.","With the aid of an assistant, use ","service tool T3880067"," to compress the fork spring, detach the spring stopper from the top cap and insert the spring holder between the lock nut and the spring stopper as shown below.","T3880067 - Fork Spring Compressor","Spring holder","Lock nut","Spring stopper","Lubricate the small O-ring on the top cap with a smear of fork oil.","Remove ","service tool T3880085"," and fit the fork top cap fully onto the damper rod and tighten by hand.","Tighten the lock nut onto the top cap to ","20 Nm",".","Lock nut","Top cap","Remove the spring holder plate and ","service tool T3880067",". Make sure the lower end of the spring stopper fit inside the spring collar and fits over the top cap.","Spring stopper","Spring collar","Top cap","Lubricate the O-ring on the top cap with a smear of fork oil.","Screw the top cap into the outer tube and using service tool tighten to ","35 Nm",".","Refit the fork (see ","Front Fork - Installation",").","Perform the following operations:","Front Fork - Installation","Inform the rider that maintenance has been carried out on the forks .","Confirm with the rider that the settings are set to their personal preference.","Riding with unfamiliar fork settings may cause unexpected handling characteristics leading to loss of motorcycle control and an accident."],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType09","createdAt":"2024-07-10T09:03:19.350Z","updatedAt":"2024-07-10T09:03:19.350Z","__v":0}